Git Commands

WORKING AREA -------------------------------------------> STAGING AREA -----------------------> LOCAL REPOSITORY
             git add. (or) git add * (or) git add filename             git commit -m "First Commit"

Step by step process:

Install git in linux server --> open gitbash --> enter git --version --> if not installed, enter sudo yum install git -y.

Enter cd ~/Desktop --> Create a directory --> mkdir pavan --> cd pavan --> pwd --> ls -al

1. git init --> initialising git repository
 
Create vi filename1 --> vi filename2 --> vi filename3 

2. git status --> to see the status of git.

3. git add . (or) git add * (or) git add filename1 filename2 filename3 
using the above 3 commands we move the files from WORKING AREA to STAGING AREA.

4. git status

5. git commit -m "First Commit" --> this command used to move the files from STAGING AREA to LOCAL REPOSITORY.

6. git config --global user.name "      " --> see username in github
   git config --global user.email "      " --> see email in github
   git config --global --list --> to see the username and email

7. git remote add fb http url --> here fb is aliasname of facebook, http url is remote repository's HTTP url
   git remote -v
   
8. To push the files from local repo to remote repo, before that it will ask username and password of github.
 (Here password is token, which is : 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

9. git log --> its shows the commit id's

10. git commit -a -m "SECOND COMMIT (or)updated filename"

11. git diff commitid1 commitid2 --> to see the difference between the commities
